      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a41ab224_042b6a6d",
        "filename": "build/find_mac_sdk.py",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 29,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:07:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We shouldn’t be building up SDK paths manually.\n\n“xcrun --show-sdk-path” will assemble a path to the default SDK.\n\n“xcrun --show-sdk-path --sdk macosx10.12” will assemble a path to the 10.12 SDK.\n\nSince you won’t be doing anything with the output other than just reprinting it, you can move from subprocess.check_output to subprocess.check_call.",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ae5a2dbb_5bbdb8e4",
        "filename": "build/find_mac_sdk.py",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:07:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "You don’t have to, but I prefer to invoke main with sys.argv[1:], and to then just use those args directly in main() without having to worry about skipping [0].",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "12500aaf_a98a48af",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:07:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don’t want to have a hard-coded default for this. See comments in the .py file.\n\nWhy? For the past few years, Apple’s only been shipping a single SDK version with each copy of Xcode. The Xcode 8 series contains the macOS 10.12 SDK, and I guess that’s what you’re using. But Xcode 9 is current, and it contains the macOS 10.13 SDK. It’s not necessarily entirely unreasonable for you (or someone else) to be using Xcode 8 still, but neither is it unreasonable for someone else to be using 9 as I am. And the only way to support both in the same tree without requiring everyone to write their SDK version down in args.gn is to respect whatever happens to be present as the default.",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cd48d767_7331451d",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:48:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, OK. How about for now I just don\u0027t pass anything in at all then, and it\u0027ll use whatever xcrun says is the default? Then the script is just a trivial GN-required wrapper around xcrun. We can add fancier overriding to downlevel when someone needs it.",
      "parentUuid": "12500aaf_a98a48af",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41938d35_69eb9f8a",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T23:03:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Ah, OK. How about for now I just don\u0027t pass anything in at all then, and it\u0027ll use whatever xcrun says is the default? Then the script is just a trivial GN-required wrapper around xcrun. We can add fancier overriding to downlevel when someone needs it.\n\nThat’s fine as long as we don’t support a user-configurable mac_sdk for the rest of the build.",
      "parentUuid": "cd48d767_7331451d",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1cc50560_69e3e44d",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:15:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "sysroot (in the style of this .gni) may not be the most unreasonable thing to have available in the standalone Crashpad build, considering the various cross targets we want to support. You’re already working with sysroot for Fuchsia in mini_chromium’s build/BUILD.gn. Should we go ahead and do a //build/config/sysroot.gni here too, and move your find_mac_sdk.py to it? It’d eliminate this use of crashpad_in_chromium.",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9a2f3dc7_903afb33",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T22:48:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sounds reasonable. I\u0027m not sure about the mini_chromium split again here, it sort of feels like that file should live in mini_chromium if it\u0027s added since we\u0027d want to configure the rest of the build with it. Is that where you were thinking?\n\nSo... hmm. I guess what we\u0027d have to do is have it in mini_chromium somewhere, but then have a stub in build/chromium_compatibility/build/config/sysroot.gni forward to the mini_chromium one. I\u0027ll try that.",
      "parentUuid": "1cc50560_69e3e44d",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1d2d2b0a_c82095b2",
        "filename": "util/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 25,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-12-06T23:03:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Sounds reasonable. I\u0027m not sure about the mini_chromium split again here, it sort of feels like that file should live in mini_chromium if it\u0027s added since we\u0027d want to configure the rest of the build with it. Is that where you were thinking?\n\u003e \n\u003e So... hmm. I guess what we\u0027d have to do is have it in mini_chromium somewhere, but then have a stub in build/chromium_compatibility/build/config/sysroot.gni forward to the mini_chromium one. I\u0027ll try that.\n\nWhatever you think is good. As we were saying last week, a lot of the split between Crashpad and mini_chromium for GN infrastructure feels a little artificial. In my mind, we’re still in the “experimenting” phase, and it’s fine if there’s churn as we decide how and where things should live.",
      "parentUuid": "9a2f3dc7_903afb33",
      "revId": "90b3472c19ae362f7f5c036ae164616985f5073b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
